         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sandhurst ¶ Now Bendigo, Vic. ¶  ¶ Decr 27/66 ¶ Dear Doctor ¶  ¶ If you have seen the enclosed seedpods before (as I conclude you have) good and well — if not I will have had a pleasure afforded me in...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">66.12.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Shiress</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Acacia</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">salicina</seg>. Label also marked: 'Interior of Australia'.</p>
               </note>Sandhurst<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Bendigo, Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Decr 27/66</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Doctor</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you have seen the enclosed seedpods before (as I conclude you have) good and well — if not I will have had a pleasure afforded me in bringing it under your notice —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A friend of mine has been inland — nearly upon Leichardts<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Leichhardt's.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>track — and was struck by the appearance of a singular looking pendulous tree &amp; by its oleaginous pods</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He describes it as growing Mangrove like — the pods remaining attached to the stem until they strike root when it seems to go on afresh until a jungle is formed —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He has never met it before in all the course of an extensive bush experience and as he found it in an unexplored district he fancies it may not have been noticed before — which I doubt — but containing as it does a very powerful expressible essential oil together with a very acrid extractive substance it is worthy of examination in a chemical point of view —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I chewed a portion of a pod, and from my experience I should not advise you to do the same, for its acridity affected my throat for hours severely and its bitter remained for a long time</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not having received all of the specimens of pyrites yet I can only apologise for the delay</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">yours ever truely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Willm<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Shiress</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
